.TH AUTOFORMAT 1 "2026-06-30" "checkrun" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
autoformat \- format supported files through Checkrun policy
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B autoformat
.RI [ -h | --help ]
.I file
.RI [ file ...]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B autoformat
formats each supplied file with the Checkrun-selected formatter for that
filetype. Unsupported files, ignored files, missing files, and files whose
formatter is not installed are skipped rather than treated as hard failures.
.PP
Editor integrations normally call this command through
.BR checkrun " " format
or through Sley's hook API. Direct use is still useful for scripts that already
have an explicit path list.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.BR -h ", " --help
Show usage and supported file types.
.SH ENVIRONMENT
.TP
.B CHECKRUN_CONFIG_DIR
Directory for local Checkrun ignore and schema policy.
.TP
.B CHECKRUN_PYTHON
Python interpreter used by Python-backed Checkrun helpers.
.SH EXIT STATUS
.TP
.B 0
Formatting completed, selected formatter failures were surfaced on stderr, or
all files were skipped for non-fatal reasons. Formatter failures are advisory
so save-time hooks do not block the caller.
.TP
.B 1
Required Checkrun infrastructure such as
.B yq
was unavailable.
.TP
.B 2
Usage error or registry planning failure.
.TP
.B 127
A required runtime dependency, such as a suitable Python interpreter, is missing.
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR checkrun (1),
.BR autolint (1)
